  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Generally, actions do not call public methods on nodes. For example, if you want to subclass "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sknode"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to respond to a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skaction/1417768-moveto"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " action, you might consider overriding its "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sknode/1483101-position"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property to add a "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "didSet"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " observer (see "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "Overriding Property Observers",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/Swift/Conceptual/Swift_Programming_Language/Inheritance.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40014097-CH17-ID201"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ")."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "class MovingNode: SKSpriteNode {",
            "    override var position: CGPoint {",
            "        didSet {",
            "            // code to react to position change",
            "        }",
            "    }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "2982294",
            "title": "Listing 1"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "However, because a move action that's running on an instance of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "MovingNode"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " (defined in the code listing above) doesn't set its position, the observer isn't invoked and thus, your code is never executed."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In this case, the solution is to use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skscenedelegate"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and compare the node's position across two of its callbacks. You save the node's initial position in "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skscenedelegate/1519757-update"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", which is called at the beginning of each frame, then calculate any change in position in "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skscenedelegate/1520071-didevaluateactionsforscene"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", which is called after actions have been evaluated. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The following code demonstrates an example of this strategy: "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "let node = SKNode()",
            "var nodePosition = CGPoint()",
            "     ",
            "func update(_ currentTime: TimeInterval, for scene: SKScene) {",
            "    nodePosition = node.position",
            "}",
            "     ",
            "func didEvaluateActions(for scene: SKScene) {",
            "    let distance = hypot(node.position.x - nodePosition.x,",
            "                         node.position.y - nodePosition.y)",
            "    ",
            "    if distance > 0 {",
            "        // code to react to position change",
            "    }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "2982298",
            "title": "Listing 2"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
